text: Kestilä is a former municipality in Northern Ostrobothnia, Finland. Since 2009, it became a part of the new municipality of Siikalatva. As of 31 December 2008, 1,574 people lived there. Neighbouring municipalities were Kajaani, Liminka, Muhos, Pyhäntä and Vaala. It was founded in 1867. == Other websites == * Municipality of Kestilä – Official website Category:1867 establishments in Finland Category:Former municipalities of Finland
